CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, February 14, 1938, pg. 22, reads: "Husband Louis Jordan Jones, Mrs. Ada Harris, wife of the prominent "Woogie" and Lena Jones descend the runway steps where the coming screen luminary boarded the TWA luxury liner that took her to Hollywood and cinema fame."
TitMainTitle: Ada Harris, wife of William "Woogie" Harris, Lena Horne's husband Louis Jones, and Lena Horne holding Harris's coat, in Allegheny County airport
